rest_of_day_open: Pretty okay, I'm going to have a fun time during the fourth of July with my Family and some friends coming over. I get to grill outside which I love. I'll probably be a little stressed since I have to write a final exam on Sunday but over all it should be and okay weekend.
critical_positive: My partner was really good at listening and keeping up with what I was saying. We had a lot of overlap with our musical interests. We were also able to kind of keep the flow going for quite a while without too much effort. At the twenty minute mark was when I first bothered to look at the time.
critical_negative: Well my partner was good at listening but I felt I was talking too much. I asked them if they had anything they wanted to talk about and they weren't sure. I think they like hearing other people talk which is what I normally do. I struggled to come up with more things but not dominate the conversation.

rest_of_day_open: For me I see it going really well. While my conversation wasn’t life changing, I got to hear some cool stories that made me smile and laugh, I’ll definitely be thinking about that alpaca farm he told me about a few times and laugh to myself about it. He gave me some recommendations for music that I will most definitely check out and think of him with!
critical_positive: I’m not a huge small talker, I really just like listening to people and hearing their stories. He’s a good storyteller so I think both those elements helped conversation occur. I also put the conversation to music since I think it’s a topic we all can find some sort of common ground or talking point. He was also just a warm person who just had an energy of kindness and likeability, making it easier to talk.
critical_negative: I don’t think anything necessarily. Like I said before I’m not the greatest small talker, so I wish I would have had more to give when he was talking about his jobs, etc., but I didn’t have any stories of my own. Because of that I didn’t feel like I had anything to contribute other than typical nods and “mhmm” when listening.
